23/01/23, 2:17 pm - Sunny '22: #include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h> // For exit()

int main()
{
	FILE *fptr1, *fptr2;
	char filename[100], c;

	printf("Enter the filename to open for reading \n");
	scanf("%s", filename);

	// Open one file for reading
	fptr1 = fopen(filename, "r");
	if (fptr1 == NULL)
	{
		printf("Cannot open file %s \n", filename);
		exit(0);
	}

	printf("Enter the filename to open for writing \n");
	scanf("%s", filename);

	// Open another file for writing
	fptr2 = fopen(filename, "w");
	if (fptr2 == NULL)
	{
		printf("Cannot open file %s \n", filename);
		exit(0);
	}

	// Read contents from file
	c = fgetc(fptr1);
	while (c != EOF)
	{
		fputc(c, fptr2);
		c = fgetc(fptr1);
	}

	printf("\nContents copied to %s", filename);

	fclose(fptr1);
	fclose(fptr2);
	return 0;
}
23/01/23, 2:17 pm - Sunny '22: struct customer {
    char name[50];
    float purchase;
};

struct customer customers[100];

int main() {
    int n; // number of customers
    float total = 0;

    // populate the array of structures with customer details
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        printf("Enter customer name: ");
        scanf("%s", customers[i].name);
        printf("Enter purchase amount: ");
        scanf("%f", &customers[i].purchase);
    }

    // calculate total purchases
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        total += customers[i].purchase;
    }

    printf("Total purchases: %.2f", total);
    return 0;
}

About Long Shot 

Long Shot is India's premier freelancing platform for finance professionals seeking short-term and long-term professional assignments.

Our platform caters to a wide range of opportunities, including stock audits, physical verification, internal audits, valuation, project reports, forensic audits, statutory registrations, and direct & indirect tax assignments. With over 15,000 partners across 28 states and 1000+ cities in India, we serve CA, CS, CMA, CISA, MBA, B.COM professionals, and students pursuing finance-related courses.

Why join Long Shot?

1. Flexibility: Choose assignments ranging from as short as 1 day to 12 months, and even work on weekends for that extra income.
2. Growth: Enhance your skills and gain diverse experience working with various audit and consulting firms and corporates.
3. Networking: Build lasting connections with industry professionals to expand your career prospects.
Security: Receive timely payments upon assignment completion and confirmation.
